# Performance & Scaling

## Targets (BR-SYS-001..004)

| Metric | Target |
|--------|--------|
| API p95 | < 2s at 5,000 CCU |
| Uptime | ≥ 99.5% / month |
| Throughput | 100,000+ reports total |
| RPO | ≤ 24h |
| RTO | ≤ 4h |

## Mandatory rules

- **Pagination on EVERY list endpoint.** Never return unbounded lists.
  - Default `pageSize=20`, max `100`. Cursor-based for very large.
- **Projection for queries** — `.ProjectToType<DTO>()` (Mapster) or `Select(...)`. Don't hydrate full entities only to map.
- **`AsNoTracking()`** for read-only queries.
- **No N+1.** Use `.Include()` with intent or projection.
- **Response compression** — Brotli enabled in `Program.cs`.
- **Heavy work → background jobs** — AI calls, notifications, exports go through Hangfire / outbox.

## Caching (Redis)

| Endpoint | TTL | Key pattern |
|----------|-----|-------------|
| Public hotspots | 10 min | `map:hotspots:{bbox}:{filters}` |
| Public map data | 10 min | `map:nearby:{bbox}:{filters}` (BR-MAP-012) |
| Leaderboard | 5 min | `gamification:leaderboard:{period}` |
| Categories / dropdowns | 1 hour | `catalog:categories` |

Invalidate on writes (e.g. new report verified → invalidate hotspot keys for that area).

## Anti-patterns

```csharp
// ❌ N+1
var reports = await db.Reports.ToListAsync(ct);
foreach (var r in reports)
    r.Comments = await db.Comments.Where(c => c.ReportId == r.Id).ToListAsync(ct);

// ❌ Unbounded list
return await db.Reports.ToListAsync(ct);

// ❌ Synchronous-over-async
var u = db.Users.FirstOrDefault(x => x.Id == id);   // missing async
```

## Index discipline

Add indexes for any new column used in `WHERE`, `ORDER BY`, or `JOIN`. Justify each index in the migration comment.

## DB connection pool

- Pool size = `2 * cpu_count + effective_spindle_count`. Default ~50 for our workload.
- Use `Npgsql` connection multiplexing for high-concurrency reads.

## Streaming exports (BR-OFF-022)

```csharp
public async IAsyncEnumerable<ReportCsvRow> StreamAsync(
    [EnumeratorCancellation] CancellationToken ct)
{
    await foreach (var r in db.Reports.AsAsyncEnumerable().WithCancellation(ct))
        yield return Map(r);
}
```
